iefs from antiquity to his contemporary moment of the early 1970s. He also charts the tongue-in-cheek activities of the Flat Earth Society of Canada, which he co-founded in 1970 with celebrated authors Alden Nowlan and Raymond Fraser. Other notable members included literary luminaries Al Pittman, Farley Mowat, Gwendolyn MacEwen, and Patrick Lane. The author blurs the line between seriousness and humour in the interests of exploring philosophical concepts such as the nature of belief and the implications of technological modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aFlat Earth Society of Canada.  aFogo Island.  aalternate fact.  afake news.  aflat earth thinking.  afour corners of the world.  aglobularism.  aplanoterrestrialism.  areality.  asatire.1 aBurns, Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurns, Kay, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEso, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEso, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTaylor, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978189472560640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781894725606423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781894725606/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles